{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F001","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The terminal v1.15 attempt is scoped exactly: every preclaim gate passed, the formal root remained empty, and the accepted-binding rehearsal failed before outcome production because the independent outer reader imposed a 64 MiB whole-file limit on each of five production-scale producer files. No v1.15 performance outcome is used to authorize or interpret v1.16."},{"id":"F002","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The outer launcher now streams every producer file once with constant-size buffers, exact per-file and aggregate bounds, exact length and digest checks, stable descriptor and inode custody, complete tree equality, and rejection of links, mutation, growth, shrinkage, and short reads."},{"id":"F003","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Decisive tests traverse the real streamed verification path at 64 MiB and 64 MiB plus one byte, exercise five sparse production roles together, invoke the real outer subprocess with an accepted binding, and cover metadata, ordering, duplication, limit, link, and concurrent-mutation failures."},{"id":"F004","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The already finalized canonical development-result-qualification object is now preserved as an exact archived sidecar, while its existing digest remains in the unchanged binding and raw-result representations; this closes custody without introducing a self-referential schema change."},{"id":"F005","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The outer launcher independently verifies exact qualification semantics, joins the raw-result qualification digest to the binding, and requires byte-identical live, copied, archived, and binding-authorized qualification custody before formal execution."},{"id":"F006","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The independent artifact auditor reconstructs the qualification joins across the live attempt, formal copy, archive, binding, and streamed raw result, and rejects extra hardlinks or custody substitutions at each producer boundary."},{"id":"F007","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"An exact post-binding, pre-formal-root rehearsal now runs the accepted binding through the real outer launcher using the result-free bootstrap inventory command, requires canonical stdout and byte-empty stderr, and proves that no formal root, marker, audit, review, or adjudication path is created."},{"id":"F008","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"Coverage is deliberately compositional and bounded: real launcher, producer, archive, audit, qualification, and authorization paths are exercised at their decisive boundaries, but no claim is made that one heavyweight fixture reproduces the complete production lifecycle end to end before the prospective run."},{"id":"F009","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Scientific continuity is exact: all 17 canonical scientific protocol blocks and the model, learning, planning, and runtime-lane kernel hashes remain frozen from the corrected predecessor."},{"id":"F010","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Representation continuity is exact: protocol v9, formal-binding v10, raw-result v9, preformal and prebinding v2, closure v2, runtime-seal v1, and preflight v1 remain unchanged because the repair strengthens custody rather than scientific meaning."},{"id":"F011","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Fresh v1.16 derivation yields 10 unique current master seeds and 1,360 unique current stream seeds, with zero collisions internally or against 150 prior masters and 20,400 prior streams through v1.15; direct predecessor lineage is pinned exactly."},{"id":"F012","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The plan and runbook freeze build, review, path-absence, prospective-test, preformal, binding, rehearsal, formal-launch, audit, semantic-review, and adjudication order, including the rule that the formal root is created only after the accepted-binding rehearsal succeeds."},{"id":"F013","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The assurance boundary remains explicit and not tamper resistant: repository, environment, path, filesystem, base-interpreter, kernel, and cooperative-lock integrity are trusted, and hashes do not provide external attestation against a same-principal or privileged adversary."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1638,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"2acc7488743eda77caee84cf98fd04693335f93b9db4331014a4576fefd0f79f"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistemic/maturity.py","sha256":"2a81abe60f12285f66f2bcd351589de28851412f1d9df7f2003843a845a2510e"},{"bytes":13611,"path":"bench/epistemic/problem.py","sha256":"c66ae13d3e833ffd1be1562a89e0e9035d6197b95723179b930c1ca2a1059c66"},{"bytes":1097,"path":"bench/epistemic/run_maturity.py","sha256":"86ae2c3175262f559a274827c96c30212fbdb9250e3a4614f92c861b7498feb7"},{"bytes":20656,"path":"bench/epistemic/runtime_lane.py","sha256":"d8f0c7a85be786c3a813ee1f169abcbc2791a642e46fba5978f7a1140cc50387"},{"bytes":278,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/SEALED_PROTOCOL.sha256","sha256":"1069df8275f77f4c822ba40497419319a2402410fc648f4abf5898b810657044"},{"bytes":75,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/__init__.py","sha256":"0390d290ffee36c3e2a696938bab498fddba3991f970676e20a0cfe0d77dba83"},{"bytes":173718,"path":"bench/world_model_lifecycle/adjudication.py","sha256":"bf1469e33937721b9bc6ceb28be03d35418f41781328490cc4a94474bbe3e6d0"},{"bytes":102884,"pat